# E-Commerce API

This is a simple E-Commerce API built using Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and Mongoose. It provides endpoints for managing users and products.

## Features

- Create, Read, Update, and Delete (CRUD) operations for users and products.
- MongoDB Atlas integration for data storage.
- Mongoose for data modeling.
- Secure and structured API routes.

## Prerequisites

Before running the API, make sure you have the following installed:

- Node.js: [Download](https://nodejs.org/)
- MongoDB Atlas: [Sign Up](https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas)

## Getting Started

1. Clone this repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/e-commerce-api.git


### Navigate to the project directory:
<!-- ```bash
cd e-commerce-api -->


### Install dependencies:


npm install 

### Create a .env file in the project root and add your MongoDB Atlas connection string as follows:


MONGODB_URI=your-mongodb-atlas-connection-string
 

### Start the API server:


npm start
 

### The server will start at

http://localhost:8080
 

 ## API Endpoints



*GET /api/users: Get all users.

*POST /api/users: Create a new user.

*PUT /api/users/:uid: Update a user by ID.

*DELETE /api/users/:uid: Delete a user by ID. -->

###  Products


*GET /api/products: Get all products.

*POST /api/products: Create a new product.

*PUT /api/products/:pid: Update a product by ID.

*DELETE /api/products/:pid: Delete a product by ID. -->

### Usage

You can use a tool like Postman to test the API endpoints. Import the provided Postman collection for easier testing.


